<br>
I generally use a 3.6 Spd Sabre in my right hand, and a 3.2 Spd Sidi Simitar in my left, when spilling blood in RvR. Just so you know. I'm not sure what the Spd is on that Rapier, but i'm guessing it's rather fast. The faster you swing, the less damage you'll do per swing.<br>
<br>
Also, if your left and right hands are roughly the same Spd, yes, you'll see about the same unstyled damage from the left and right hand. But, if the right hand weapon is at all slower (Yes, even 0.2 Spd difference makes a noiticable difference) the the off-hand, you will see bigger hits from the right hand, period. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> DPS.</span><hr size=1> What's the DPS on that quest Rapier?  I remember getting it, looking at it, and quickly salvaging it.  I'm pretty sure it's not 16.5 DPS either way.<br>
